definition.value: An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of ascr#3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of ascr#3-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of ascr#7.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of ascr#7-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is conjugate base of ascr#9 resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major species at pH 7.3.
